PI. Having to define the shortcuts yourself is less convenient than having<br>&gt; them come with the library.<br>&gt;<br>&gt; Moreover, the IDE could even help you by showing you what you can type<br>&gt; using standard characters to generate a particular unicode identifier as<br>&gt; can be automatically determined via unicodealiases in the library source.<br>&gt;<br>&gt; Best,<br>&gt; Jordan<br>&gt;<br>&gt; P.S. As a general note, please include in the first message for a feature<br>&gt; *why* you think a particular feature is a good idea for Swift. That saves<br>&gt; a bit of time for those of us who may not immediately see the benefit.<br>&gt;<br>&gt; _______________________________________________<br>&gt; swift-evolution mailing list<br>&gt; swift-evolution at swift.org<br>&gt; https://lists.swift.org/mailman/listinfo/swift-evolution<br>&gt;<br>-------------- next part --------------<br>An HTML attachment was scrubbed...<br>URL: &lt;https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-evolution/attachments/20160116/183c49a4/attachment.html&gt;<br></p></div></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></div>    </main>
